Q19: What does it mean to "containerize" an application, and how can using
containers help when building microservices? Also, briefly explain what
Kubernetes is.

The containerization process means that the application processes are segregated on multiple user spaces, running on the same kernel space. Kuberentes is a pod manager and container orchestrator, keeping all the depoyment objects into a one place: Deployment, Configmap, VirtualService, etc. Kube is taking care of all the running objects inside a cluster, working as a system scheduler. (e.g. CronJobs, Daemons, etc).


